The paper discusses research related to data warehousing, OLAP, and data mining, which are all subfields of database systems (cs.DB). The focus of the paper is on extracting and analyzing data from the web, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of XML as a logical and physical model for complex data warehouses is a topic related to deep learning (cs.DL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses schema evolution in complex data warehouses, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
